1
00:00:00,209 --> 00:00:02,201
Previously on Kyle XY

2
00:00:02,287 --> 00:00:03,636
Adam wanted me to give you this.

3
00:00:03,716 --> 00:00:05,520
- What's the symbol?
- Never seen it before.

4
00:00:05,643 --> 00:00:07,836
- What is it?
- The company was sold this morning.

5
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:09,169
What does this mean?

6
00:00:09,249 --> 00:00:10,458
I just lost my job.

7
00:00:11,127 --> 00:00:13,722
XY's brain is powerful,
much like a computer.

8
00:00:13,808 --> 00:00:16,546
We need what Kyle knows.
That's where she comes in.

9
00:00:16,626 --> 00:00:18,111
What, like a mental hacker?

10
00:00:18,236 --> 00:00:19,759
In a manner of speaking, yes.

11
00:00:19,845 --> 00:00:21,580
She thinks that she's my sister.

12
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:23,556
I'm just supposed to live that lie?

13
00:00:23,636 --> 00:00:25,376
Destabilizing the boy's
support structure

14
00:00:25,456 --> 00:00:27,986
will make him more vulnerable,
receptive to her.

15
00:00:28,072 --> 00:00:29,572
Get her into that family's life.

16
00:00:29,658 --> 00:00:32,175
My sister Jessi,
she's been having some problems,

17
00:00:32,255 --> 00:00:34,515
and I was hoping you might
be able to sit down with her.

18
00:00:34,613 --> 00:00:36,076
I think I might be able to help you.

19
00:00:36,162 --> 00:00:37,761
Jessi's got herself a therapist.

20
00:00:37,859 --> 00:00:38,916
What is this?

21
00:00:39,002 --> 00:00:40,167
It's your new car.

22
00:00:40,247 --> 00:00:41,616
I thought we could work on it.

23
00:00:41,702 --> 00:00:43,928
Why don't you come over later?
I'll be home around 4.

24
00:00:44,026 --> 00:00:47,370
If you don't show up,
then I know there's nothing left to say.

25
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:52,601
Where the hell is he going?

26
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:04,502
About Charlie...

27
00:01:04,588 --> 00:01:06,442
I should have told you
what was going on.

28
00:01:06,522 --> 00:01:10,404
Yeah, well, being someone's friend
isn't about what you should have done...

29
00:01:10,834 --> 00:01:12,179
it's about what you do.

30
00:01:19,765 --> 00:01:21,954
Foss calls it sensory deprivation.

31
00:01:22,925 --> 00:01:24,450
The removal of all other senses

32
00:01:24,536 --> 00:01:27,062
to enhance the one sense that remains.

33
00:01:28,186 --> 00:01:31,286
As I focused on the nighttime
sounds that surrounded me,

34
00:01:31,483 --> 00:01:34,515
the world became more vid
than it ever had before.

35
00:01:34,629 --> 00:01:36,348
So did the people around me.

36
00:01:37,383 --> 00:01:39,088
I could sense things,

37
00:01:39,168 --> 00:01:41,761
like the guilt and uncertainty
over losing a job.

38
00:01:45,548 --> 00:01:48,812
Or the anxiety and self-doubt
over starting a new one.

39
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:55,421
Even staying up way past bedtime
to spend time with a new friend.

40
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:59,506
Or the first sparks of creativity...

41
00:01:59,638 --> 00:02:02,539
which can't quite mask the pain
over a break-up.

42
00:02:03,695 --> 00:02:06,941
But soon the walls of the Trager house
began to disappear...

43
00:02:09,777 --> 00:02:12,790
and I could hear past
the symphony of crickets...

44
00:02:13,896 --> 00:02:15,900
all the way into Amanda's house

45
00:02:16,207 --> 00:02:18,961
where I could hear the soft
pounding of her heart.

46
00:02:21,593 --> 00:02:24,722
It seemed even a broken heart
still beats the same.

47
00:02:27,389 --> 00:02:29,159
But there was another heartbeat.

48
00:02:29,257 --> 00:02:30,510
It was different,

49
00:02:30,805 --> 00:02:31,875
erratic.

50
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:44,239
- Are you all right?
- There was a man.

51
00:02:44,337 --> 00:02:45,678
He's getting away.

52
00:03:02,658 --> 00:03:04,203
The thing about sensory deprivation

53
00:03:04,283 --> 00:03:06,764
is you can use it to enhance
any of the senses.

54
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:08,179
But like my hearing,

55
00:03:08,265 --> 00:03:10,564
in order to increase
what my eyes could see,

56
00:03:10,687 --> 00:03:12,900
I had to tune out all of
my other senses...

57
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,992
until the only thing left was my vision.

58
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:22,518
Otherwise I would have
heard the car start.

